Install: (pip2 - bo volality dziala na python2)
→ apt-get install yara
→ apt-get install python3-dev
→ pip2 install pycrypto
→ pip2 install cryptography
→ pip2 install distorm3
→ pip2 install crypto
→ pip2 install cryptohash
→ pip2 install pycrypto
→ cd /opt
→ git clone https://github.com/volatilityfoundation/volatility.git
→ cd volatility
→ make
→ make install
→ python2 vol.py -h     (Sprawdzenie czy dziala i czy nie wyswietla bledow)
→ echo ‘python2 /opt/volatility/vol.py $1 $2 $3 $4 $5 $6 $7 $8 $9’ >> /usr/bin/vol 
→ chmod +x /usr/bin/vol
→ I teraz normalnie w konsoli “vol”
